Iavan Pijoos, News24(Picture: Netcare 911) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A 11-year-old boy was airlifted to hospital after he was bitten by a lion in Laphelale, Limpopo on Saturday afternoon, paramedics said. &nbsp;The incident happened at 12:45 on Saturday.Netcare911 spokesperson Chris Botha said he was in a serious condition and was rushed to a local hospital in the area where he underwent treatment. &nbsp; &ldquo;Netcare helicopter landed at the hospital and after they stabilised him for the flight, they airlifted him under the constant care of two emergency care practitioners to a specialised hospital in Pretoria,&rdquo; Botha said.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.